Sony Interactive Entertainment has announced its Black Friday deals, which include significant deals for a variety of products including games and PlayStation Plus subscriptions. PlayStation gamers can expect up to 60% off a host of popular titles during Black Friday, including the critically-acclaimed new release Red Dead Redemption 2, Marvelâ€™s Spider-Man, Call of Duty: Black Ops 4, and FIFA 19. This sale will end at midnight GMT on 26 November. A 12-month subscription to PlayStation Plus will be discounted by 20%, while a three-month subscription will cost 15% less. These subscription deals will run until 12:00 on 27 November, and are available to both new and existing members. Sony added that it plans to announce more Black Friday PlayStation deals soon.